  <a href="#1" id="1">
   Edgar Bronfman, President of the World Jewish Congress, announced a scheduled conference in the Berlin villa
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   where Nazi leadership met to implement the "final solution" against Europe's Jews.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   The purpose is to formulate a formal declaration regarding German reunification.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   He said
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   that a part of their planned moral statement
  </a>
  <a href="#6" id="6">
   to be made on May 8 is to see
  </a>
  <a href="#7" id="7">
   that the Holocaust cannot happen again.
  </a>
  <a href="#8" id="8">
   Bronfman said
  </a>
  <a href="#9" id="9">
   he doesn't fear a resurgence of anti-Semitism from a united Germany;
  </a>
  <a href="#10" id="10">
   in fact, reunification may cause a decline in anti-Jewish feeling.
  </a>
  <a href="#11" id="11">
   They won't be blaming Jews for a divided Germany,
  </a>
  <a href="#12" id="12">
   he explained.
  </a>
